# Docker Hub Pro Personal Access Token (PAT) for pulling
# docker.io/lfds/audittrace-content-control:* (and any future
# private images under the lfds namespace).
#
# 1. Create a PAT at https://app.docker.com/settings/personal-access-tokens
#    Access permissions: Read, Write, Delete (account-wide).
#    Expiry: 90 days (rotate quarterly).
#
# 2. Paste ONLY the PAT below (replacing this placeholder); save as
#    ./secrets/docker_hub_pat.txt (the .txt suffix is gitignored;
#    .example is committed as a template).
#
# 3. Run `make k8s-bootstrap-secrets` (which re-runs setup-vault.sh
#    + restarts the Vault Agent injector). The PAT lands in
#    Vault path kv/audittrace/docker-hub/pat.
#
# 4. The chart template `secret-dockerhub-pull.yaml` then renders
#    the `audittrace-dockerhub-pull` k8s Secret of type
#    kubernetes.io/dockerconfigjson. The audittrace-content-control
#    sibling chart references this Secret name in its
#    imagePullSecrets list.
#
# Rotation: replace the PAT, re-run setup-vault.sh, recreate the
# k8s Secret. See ADR-048 PR-B2 commit + the Vault audit log.
dckr_pat_REPLACE_WITH_REAL_TOKEN
